= Design and Methodology

This section of the dissertation may vary significantly in both structure and content, depending on the type of project you are undertaking. Many MSc projects involve both a software artefact and a research component — in such cases, it is helpful to split this chapter into two distinct parts, as shown below. The precise structure should be discussed with your supervisor.

The key thing to note here is that irrespective of the project type, you should justify the choices you have made with academic reasoning, rather than simply choosing based on expediency or familiarity.

== Part A: Research Methodology

If your project involves a user study or empirical research, this section should detail your research design. The following subsections are recommended:

=== Experimental Design

Describe and justify your research design (e.g., within-subjects, between-subjects, mixed methods). Explain your design rationale and why this approach is appropriate for answering your research questions.

=== Participants

Detail your approach to participant recruitment, including sample size determination (e.g., power analysis), recruitment strategy, and eligibility criteria (both inclusion and exclusion). If applicable, describe demographics collection methods.

=== Measures and Instruments

Describe the instruments and measures used to collect data (e.g., validated questionnaires, custom surveys, physiological sensors). Justify the selection of each instrument with reference to the literature.

=== Procedure

Describe the step-by-step procedure that participants follow during your study, in enough detail that it could be replicated.

=== Data Analysis Plan

Describe how you plan to analyse the collected data. For quantitative data, specify the statistical tests you will use and why. For qualitative data, describe your analysis approach (e.g., thematic analysis).

=== Ethical Considerations

Describe the ethical considerations of your study and confirm that appropriate ethical approval has been obtained. Reference any ethics documentation in the appendices.

== Part B: Software Development

This section covers the design and development methodology for the software artefact.

=== Software Engineering Methodology

Describe and justify the software development methodology used (e.g., agile, waterfall, scrum). Explain why this approach was suitable for the project.

=== Risk Analysis

Document the risks associated with the project and how they were mitigated. Consider both technical risks (e.g., hardware failure, software bugs) and project risks (e.g., time constraints, scope creep).

=== Toolsets and Environments

Detail the software tools, frameworks, libraries, and hardware environments used in the project, and justify their selection.

=== Design

Present the design of your software system (e.g., UML diagrams, database schemas, system architecture diagrams, wireframes, prototypes). For games projects, this may include a game design document.

=== Testing

Describe the types of testing used (e.g., unit testing, integration testing, user acceptance testing) and your approach to quality assurance.
